3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-402 of Title 26, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. 1. As used in this section, "new federal election funds"
7 means any federal grant, appropriation by the United States
8 Congress, or other federal funds that are eligible to be received by
9 the Secretary of the State Election Board or the secretary of a
10 county election board on or after the effective date of this act.
11 2. Provided, new federal election funds shall not mean funding
12 or grants provided under the Help America Vote Act, other federal
13 funding or grants are authorized to be accepted by state law, or any
14 Cybersecurity or Physical Security subgrants provided by the
15 Oklahoma Office of Homeland Security.
16 B. Except as provided in paragraph 2 of subsection A of this
17 section, all new federal election funds must be approved by the
18 State Legislature before they may be accepted or used by the
19 Secretary of the State Election Board or the secretary of a county
20 election board. Provided, if the Legislature is not in session when
21 new federal election funds become available, new federal election
22 funds may be accepted upon the written approval of the Speaker of
23 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of
24 the Oklahoma State Senate, the Chair of the Senate Appropriations
