3 C. No later than January 15, 2026, and each year thereafter,
4 the Secretary of the State Election Board shall publish on the State
5 Election Board's website the balance of all federal funds possessed
6 by the State Election Board for the previous two (2) years and a
7 description of the source of those funds. Provided, in the event
8 that January 15 of any year falls on a weekend or an official state
9 holiday, such information shall be published the next business day.
10 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 16-114, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 16-114. Any member or employee of the State Election
13 Board, a county election board, absentee voting board or any
14 precinct official who willfully fails to perform his or her lawful
15 duty shall be deemed guilty of a misdemeanor.
16 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective January 1, 2026.
